I am an expert in identifying and working with legacy file formats. I wrote [Siegfried](https://www.itforarchivists.com/siegfried), a file format identification tool, based on the National Archives' [PRONOM registry](https://nationalarchives.gov.uk/aboutapps/pronom), that is bundled with leading digital preservation systems such as [Archivematica](https://archivematica.org/)

I can analyze, reverse engineer, and develop custom migration strategies for file formats. In past roles I've tackled obscure formats such as [Wang Archive Diskette](https://github.com/richardlehane/wang), [Status database](https://futureproof.records.nsw.gov.au/saving-our-digital-history-byte-by-byte/), and [TRIM VMBX](https://github.com/srnsw/vmbx).